 class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/upetoffen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Petoffen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/18/01 2:09:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fprexus95980frm17.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=130.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://members.home.net/craig234/eq/petportrait.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Blocking arrows</span><hr size=1> When a man and a woman have special feelings for one another, and want to be together, they can do this.<br><br>Sheesh, computer game nerds.<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>Arch Mage 60, Master of the epic elemental magics, collector of robes<BR><a href="http://members.home.net/craig234/"target="web"><img src="http://members.home.net/craig234/eq/sig/adaviabigpet.gif" border="0"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uharrisonabbeyroad3.showPublicProfile?language=EN>harrisonabbeyroad3</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/18/01 4:10:52 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fprexus95980frm17.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=130.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Blocking arrows</span><hr size=1> You block arrows with your shield as long as you are facing the right direction...although I am not sure what the % to block is.<br><br>Engage is a skill you get that is &quot;poor mans crowd control&quot;. It allows you to block like 90% (or something like that) of the Mobs blows. However you don't get to fight back. I think it is just used as a last ditch effort to keep a mob occupied while the rest of the group kills the other mob. I never find it useful but that might change in RvR or if they implement an Uber Mob encounter.<br><br>Harrison Abbeyroad 20 Pally Percival Server <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usunnieeq.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SunnieEQ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/18/01 9:14:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fprexus95980frm17.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=130.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Blocking arrows</span><hr size=1> Best just to avoid archer types period.<br><br>1) Don't wear bright a** dyes into the frontier.  Stick with greens/browns.  The yellows, blues, purples, etc are like a neon sign over your head saying &quot;Please shoot me&quot;<br><br>2) Turn off that GD torch.  (See neon sign comment above)<br><br>3) Don't go out alone to the frontier.  Lone targets and small lower level groups is what the archer is looking for.<br><br>4) Stay in combat mode (F6).  Crit shots won't work.<br><br>Sunnie<br>52 druid, Prexus <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uklumzepuller.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Klumze Puller</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/19/01 2:29:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fprexus95980frm17.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=130.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Blocking arrows</span><hr size=1> With a shield equipped and if you have shield skill equal to your level you have a 30% chance to block an attack against a yellow conning mob. This chance increases as the mob's con is lower up to 60%, this is besides parry and missing. With engage your chances rise to 90% against a equal conning mob. This skill is best to &quot;Rush&quot; a archer and take him out where your melee skills are superior. This was posted on the DAOC update patch quite some time ago. I believe I havent messed any of it up as I am not quoting just paraphrasing it. <p><html><body><center><img src="http://klumze.homestead.com/files/samurai.jpg"></center></body><html> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ustinkybeef.showPublicProfile?language=EN>stinkybeef</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/19/01 2:33:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fprexus95980frm17.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=130.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Blocking arrows</span><hr size=1> Adding to what Sunnie said, take of your cloaks if you are really concerned with living from archers. Even though I never have a problem finding people without stealth, even with colors like the terrain. But for archers, its take off your cloak, turn off torches, and make sure you always get the higher ground and go through trees alot.<br><br>Rhyce <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uftos1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ftos1</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/19/01 8:27:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fprexus95980frm17.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=130.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Blocking arrows</span><hr size=1> Nice<br><br><br>                                                       Ftos Fatroll<br>                                                  46 Troll Shadowknight <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/unadeya.showPublicProfile?language=EN>nadeya</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/19/01 10:52:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fprexus95980frm17.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=130.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.earthlink.net/~giffle/eqpics/nadicon.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Blocking arrows</span><hr size=1> thot torches were client side only? <p><CENTER><IMG SRC="http://members.home.net/giffle3/sig2.jpg"></CENTER></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uzifnab.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zifnab</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/19/01 11:14:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fprexus95980frm17.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=130.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.carolina.rr.com/sg/images/tnboard/tn.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Blocking arrows</span><hr size=1> A couple of incorrect statements in sunnie's post...<br><br><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  2) Turn off that GD torch. (See neon sign comment above)</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br><br>Torches are client side.  The enemy cannot see them.<br><br><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>  4) Stay in combat mode (F6). Crit shots won't work.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br><br>Just being in combat mode does not stop crit shots.  You actually have to be engaged in a fight.<br><br><br><br> <p><b>Snide - lvl 29 Ranger</b><br><a href=http://pub31.ezboard.com/btempestnight>Tempest Night</a>, Palomides<br><font size=-1><i>"Once you go small you'll never go tall!"</i></font><br></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uzifnab.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zifnab</A> at: 11/19/01 11:15:18 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uyurian.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Yurian</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_thatch.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/19/01 1:06:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fprexus95980frm17.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=130.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> .</span><hr size=1> &quot;Torches are client side. The enemy cannot see them.&quot;<br><br>Nope.<br><br>The area illumination is client side, that's all. If you walk around at night with your torch off you'll see the difference on others. They really should add it so it is much more noticable, but it'd require alot more system overhead. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uzifnab.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zifnab</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/19/01 2:57:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fprexus95980frm17.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=130.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> Ah, I run around enemy territory with my torch on but then again I'm stealthed.<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F5F5DC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/urolastafnightstorm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rolastaf Nightstorm</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/28/01 10:54:35 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fprexus95980frm17.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=130.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> Ok, I can say for sure that if you're engaged in a fight, I cannot take a crit shot at you.  However, i can take a regular shot.<br><br>I can also say for sure that if you're engaged in a fight, it's harder to hit you with a bowshot.<br><br>I guess this factors in people jumping around and tossing and tumbling and stuff when they fight, kinda hard to get a shot off and not hit your own teammate.<br><br>I can also say from exp that if you have your torch on, it will make a lighter region on the landscape.  Sometimes this is just the landscape, but if it's moving along, you know it's a player.<br><br>(in any case, beware of the Grannies!)<br>~r~ <p><BR><i>Rola Nightstorm, Scout of Albion, Morgan Le Faye</i><a href=http://www.scaleofjustice.org><img src=http://www.nhbzone.com/up4it/up4it_images/rolasig.jpg height=122 width=400></a><BR><i>"An honest man's pillow is his peace of mind." <BR>John Mellancamp</i></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fprexus95980frm17.showPrevMessage?topicID=130.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fprexus95980frm17.showNextMessage?topicID=130.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fprexus95980frm17.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=130.topic&index=11><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/